<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old man was arrested Monday night in connection with the slaying of 
Robert Ashley Moon, who was found suffering from a gunshot wound at 8 a.m. 
April 15 in an alley in the 4100 block of 36th Street, said police spokesman 
Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Moon died that afternoon in a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested in connection with the killing was Clarence Marshall Spurlock, 19. He 
and Moon lived in a garage behind a home in the 4100 block of 36th Street. 
</P>
<P>
Spurlock was booked into County Jail, where he is being held without bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
