<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 57-year-old inmate who had been transferred to Physicians &amp; Surgeons 
Hospital from the County Jail because of a respiratory infection died Monday, 
Sheriff's Department officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Peter Ignacio Lucero, a San Diego laborer who lived in the 2700 block of 
Broadway, was booked April 3 into County Jail on suspicion of being under the 
influence of a drug, Lt. Dave Herbert said. 
</P>
<P>
Lucero was transferred to the hospital April 5, and was under a doctor's care 
until his death, Herbert said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
