<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW HAVEN REACHES CALDER CUP FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW HAVEN, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Kudelski the go-ahead goal in the second period as the New Haven Nighthawks 
advanced to the American Hockey League's Calder Cup finals for the first time 
in 10 years with a 6-2 victory over the Moncton Hawks Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Nighthawks, the top farm club of the Kings, defeated Moncton, 4-2, in the 
semifinal series and will meet the Adirondack Red Wings for the Calder Cup 
starting Thursday in Glens Falls, N.Y. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
