<P>
Gov. Mario Cuomo vetoed proposed legislation that would have permitted tuition 
increases at the four-year colleges of the City University of New York and the 
State University of New York. His action followed student protests that have 
all but shut down the City University system, but Cuomo insisted his decision, 
