and use of illegal drugs by truck drivers, state Atty. Gen. John K. Van de Kamp 
said. Similar undercover operations have been conducted in the Southern 
California and Sacramento areas, he said, with the statewide arrest total in 
the campaign now about 250. Van de Kamp said he was surprised by how openly 
methamphetamines and other drugs are sold at truck stops in California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
