<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Act III Completes Purchase of Theaters: Act III Communications, a Los 
Angeles-based communications firm controlled by veteran television producer 
Norman Lear, completed its purchase of Luxury Theatres, a chain of 293 theater 
screens in 87 locations in the West and Northwest, for an estimated $150 
million. With its other holdings, its Act III Theatres subsidiary now has 473 
screens in 114 locations in seven states, making it the ninth-largest U.S. 
motion picture exhibitor, the company said. Extensive real estate ownership was 
a major factor in the purchase, according to Scott C. Wallace, president and 
chief executive of Act III Theatres, which is based in San Antonio. 
</P>
