additional 6% of Park Ridge Corp., parent company of Hertz Corp., for $30 
million in cash. The purchase will bring Volvo's total stake in the car rental 
company to 26%. Volvo will acquire its new equity in Park Ridge from Ford Motor 
Co. The transaction is expected to close during June. Volvo bought its initial 
20% stake in Park Ridge from Ford in August, 1988. 
