<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKEND SHOOTING TAKES SECOND LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A second man has died as a result of a weekend shooting that started as an 
argument over drugs, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Rodriguez Nambo, 20, of Santa Ana died Tuesday morning at the United 
Western Medical Center-Anaheim from wounds suffered when he and another man 
where shot about 3 a.m. Saturday during an argument over drugs, Maureen Thomas, 
a Santa Ana police spokeswoman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Nambo and Marciano Garcia, 21, were shot in the 1200 block of W. Highland St. 
Garcia, shot twice was pronounced dead at the scene. He lived in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they still have no suspects in the shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
