<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RICE PITCHES 1-HITTER TO PUT FOUNTAIN VALLEY INTO SOLE POSSESSION OF FIRST 
PLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rae Rice pitched a one-hitter and Fountain Valley High School defeated Edison, 
9-0, Tuesday in a Sunset League softball game at Edison. 
</P>
<P>
The victory moved the Barons (16-5-1 overall, 5-2 in league play) into sole 
possession of first place, one game ahead of Marina and Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Rice (7-3) struck out 14 batters and allowed only a second-inning single. 
</P>
<P>
She also hit a three-run homer in the third. Shannon Dolan had two hits, two 
runs scored and an RBI for the Barons. 
</P>
<P>
In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 1, Marina 0 -- Pam Fogg (8-6) pitched a two-hitter, striking 
out four, for the Oilers (11-11, 4-3) at Huntington Beach. The Oilers took the 
lead in the second, as Sasha Kyle scored from second base on a dropped fly 
ball. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 5, Westminster 0 -- Marla Pickard (9-6) pitched a one-hitter, 
striking out four, for Ocean View (15-11, 4-3) at Westminster. Pickard allowed 
only a single by Nicole Boelm to lead off the third. Lisa Rousey hit a two-run 
homer for the Seahawks. 
</P>
<P>
In the Angelus League: 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Amat 2, Rosary 1 -- Janice Stadel had two hits and scored the only run 
for visiting Rosary. 
</P>
<P>
St. Joseph 2, Mater Dei 0 -- Lisa Fernandez pitched a one-hitter, striking out 
14, for the Jesters (8-0 in league play) at St. Joseph. Fernandez allowed only 
a third-inning single by Cathy Donohue. Bev Stighbaur and Michelle Ourique had 
RBI singles for St. Joseph. Terri Kobata (6-4) pitched a four-hitter, striking 
out seven, but took the loss for Mater Dei (14-6-2, 4-3-1). 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 10, Santa Ana Valley 0 -- Kristin Heizer (10-7) pitched a no-hitter, 
striking out nine. After a walk in the first and fifth innings accounted for 
Santa Ana Valley's only two baserunners, she retired the final nine batters. 
Heizer also went three for four with a double. Catcher Chanele Chambrone drove 
in three runs with a double and a groundout. Canyon (16-9, 6-1) is tied for 
first with Villa Park. Santa Ana Valley is 6-15 and 0-7. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park 5, Troy 0 -- Shannon Akau tossed a one-hitter, striking out 11 and 
walking none at Buena Park High School. Akau also went two for three with a run 
scored. Christina Urban had two hits and scored two runs. Buena Park improves 
to 13-3 overall and 6-1 in the league; Troy is 2-8 and 1-6. 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 2, Fullerton 0 -- Amy Huett pitched a no-hitter, striking out eight 
and walking two to outpitch Cathleen Kennedy, who allowed one earned run on two 
hits. Huett drove in the first run of the game with a single in the first 
inning that drove in Stacey Thurber from second. Sunny Hills improves to 5-2 in 
the league while Fullerton drops to 2-5. 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande 2, Pacifica 1 -- Melinda Acosta hit a bases-loaded single with one 
out in the bottom of the seventh to give Bolsa Grande (6-2, 4-7) the victory. 
Karie Benefiel (6-8) pitched a six hitter, striking out four, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 4, Los Amigos 0 -- Gina Alcoser pitched a one-hitter while going two 
for three with two runs scored for No. 2 ranked Kennedy (19-4, 10-1) at Los 
Amigos. Freshman Danielle McLeod went two for three with a double and a RBI. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 13, Santiago 3 -- Cheri Williams had a three-run homer and Jill 
Bishop had three hits and three RBIs for La Quinta (15-7, 7-4) at Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 12, Santa Margarita 4 -- Cherilyn Culp had two hits, 
including a grand slam, for the Heralds (9-6, 8-3) at Whittier Christian. 
