<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: NORTH'S NO NIELSEN HERO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The jury trying Oliver North on criminal charges is still out, but the verdict 
on him in entertainment terms is in: Thumbs down. The first part of CBS' "Guts 
&amp; Glory: The Rise and Fall of Oliver North," ran third in its time period 
Sunday night, ratings from the A.C. Nielsen Co. showed Tuesday. CBS' two-hour 
drama attracted viewers in about 12.7 million homes, compared to 16 million for 
NBC's "Bionic Showdown" and 13.7 million for ABC's "My Name Is Bill W." The 
full list of ratings for last week can be found on Page 8. 
</P>
<P>
* Lucille Ball went out a winner in the TV ratings. The news special that CBS 
broadcast about her on the night she died last Wednesday was seen in about 13.7 
million homes, compared to 11 million for ABC's "China Beach" and 10.5 million 
for NBC's "Nightingales." 
</P>
<P>
TV RATINGS 
</P>
