<P>
CENTRAL PARK JOGGER OUT OF COMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The jogger who was severely beaten and raped by a gang of youths in Central 
Park has awakened from her coma, though she remains delirious, doctors said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Doctors at Metropolitan Hospital said the 28-year-old woman was able to talk in 
a whisper to relatives and staff members, raise two fingers when asked and read 
large signs. Though she has little facial expression, she has smiled, they 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"She has been emerging gradually over the last couple of days or three days," 
said Dr. Robert S. Kurtz. "We would still say . . . she is in a delirium. 
People in this stage will fluctuate." 
</P>
<P>
Six teen-agers have been indicted on charges of attempted murder, rape, sodomy 
and assault in the April 19 attack. 
</P>
