<TEXT>
<P>
The judge in Oliver L. North's Iran-Contra trial said today he ordered longer 
working days and shorter lunches for the jury deciding the fired White House 
aide's fate. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt there was time being wasted in the sense that when they came in in the 
morning they were not starting as early as they could have," Judge Gerhard A. 
