<P>
SAILOR CLAIMS SOLO RECORD: 125 DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BREST, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
French yachtsman Olivier de Kersauzon sailed into this Atlantic port this 
morning, 125 days and 19 hours after his departure, claiming a record for the 
fastest solo sailing voyage around the world. 
</P>
<P>
Kersauzon left Brest Dec. 28 in his pink-colored trimaran named Another Look. 
He made two stops along the way for repairs, first in South Africa and then in 
Argentina. 
</P>
<P>
On his triumphant return at 8:25 a.m. today, Kersauzon was escorted by several 
French naval vessels. Fireboats sounded their sirens and sprayed jets of water 
in the air in salute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
