S.F. '49ERS WAIVE DOUG DUBOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARA, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Francisco 49ers have waived running back Doug DuBose, who finished the 
season on injured reserve. 
</P>
<P>
DuBose, in his second year out of Nebraska, injured his knee against the Los 
Angeles Rams on Dec. 18. He rushed 24 times for 116 yards and two touchdowns 
last season. 
</P>
<P>
DuBose, waived Tuesday, was suspended for four weeks of training camp before 
the 1988 season after failing a drug test. General Manager John McVay declined 
to say if the waiver was drug-related. 
</P>
