<P>
MUNICH TO HOST DAVIS CUP SEMIFINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MUNICH, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Davis Cup semifinal between West Germany and the United States will be 
played at the Olympiahalle in Munich July 21 through 23. 
</P>
<P>
The West German Tennis Federation said today that Munich was chosen over 
Dortmund because the Bavarian capital has more hotel space available. 
</P>
<P>
The Olympic hall was the site of the Davis Cup final in 1985, when Sweden beat 
West Germany. 
</P>
