<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Associated Press reported erroneously Monday that Glenn Golenberg, owner of 
Golenberg &amp; Co. of Cleveland, was among eight people who agreed to 
surrender illicit profits for alleged insider trading in Revco stock. Golenberg 
agreed to pay a $470,000 penalty, but the federal government found no evidence 
that he profited from information he gained as Revco's investment adviser. 
</P>
